{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/what-are-the-important-principles-of-data-visualization-3d3ca6c8c303", "time": 1683015395.205717, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/what-are-the-important-principles-of-data-visualization-3d3ca6c8c303/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "What are the important principles of data visualization? | by Saurav Singla | Towards Data Science", "h1": "What are the important principles of data visualization?", "description": "The architecture of the data visualization must be focused on the empowerment of your company. To do so, there are important principles that need to be practiced."}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://blog.qlik.com/visual-encoding", "anchor_text": "https://blog.qlik.com/visual-encoding", "paragraph_index": 26}, {"url": "https://www.recordedfuture.com/information-seeking-mantra/", "anchor_text": "https://www.recordedfuture.com/information-seeking-mantra/", "paragraph_index": 27}, {"url": "http://paldhous.github.io/ucb/2016/dataviz/week2.html", "anchor_text": "http://paldhous.github.io/ucb/2016/dataviz/week2.html", "paragraph_index": 28}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/SAURAVSINGLA_08", "anchor_text": "@SauravSingla_08", "paragraph_index": 32}, {"url": "http://www.linkedin.com/in/saurav-singla-5b412320", "anchor_text": "Saurav_Singla", "paragraph_index": 32}, {"url": "https://github.com/sauravsingla", "anchor_text": "SauravSingla", "paragraph_index": 32}], "all_paragraphs": ["In this article, you can explore Data Visualisation, what visual encoding techniques should be considered, how you can refine the visualization and, what do you mean by narrative visualization?", "\u201cThere is no such thing as information overload. There is only bad design.\u201d \u2014 Edward Tufte", "\u201cTo find signals in data, we must learn to reduce the noise \u2014 not just the noise that resides in the data, but also the noise that resides in us. It is nearly impossible for noisy minds to perceive anything but noise in data.\u201d \u2014 Stephen Few", "Data visualization is the process of translating raw data into graphs, images that explain numbers and allow us to gain insight into them. It shifts the way we make use of the knowledge to build meaning out of it, to find new patterns, and to identify trends.", "We, as humans, quickly comprehend information by visualization. In layman\u2019s terms, data visualization is the graphical representation of the data procured. This allows decision-makers to move more effectively on the basis of the evidence visualized and presented.", "Visualization of data can help businesses. Analyzing and incorporating data into an enterprise will give the original raw data greater significance and purpose. In the travel industry, data visualization really empowers travel administrators and consumers to report by offering transparent and actionable information into their services. The data-driven software adds benefit to all stakeholders from the finance controller to the security managers and the HR managers to the travelers themselves.", "Data visualization is one of the most critical skills for any analyst and even for businesses. No matter how good one is at analyzing data, if they cannot package it in a way that communicates what they want to present and it is not easy for people to understand, then a lot of the analysis gets lost.", "(Smyers, 2013) states that Data visualization is shaping our industry. Further,(Steele et al., no date) suggests that you can do visual encoding when you know in detail about your data.", "Colors are not naturally in order of human brains. Therefore, misuse of color should be avoided such as extra bright colors.", "According to (Few, 2006) a line graph should only be used for time-series data. It helps us to show multiple data points across time-series.", "Try showing a line chart for time series data to avoid occlusion which means hiding of data.", "(Lundblad, noDate) states that for the encoding process, length, direction, angle, area, and volume, color shading should be taken into consideration.", "According to the New York times, recent years' pie chart is avoided by the audience. Further, the vertical bar should only be used when there are few items as compared to the horizontal bar which can be used for items. Also, the Box plot gives clear results as compared to jitter plots.", "(Lillo et al., 2004) suggests that the Bezold effect should be taken into consideration while coloring data graphics. Bezold effect shows how the audience perceived colors are affected by the surrounding of the colors. It means one color changes the entire composition of the design.", "Similarly, (Bradley, 2014) states the law of Pr\u00e4gnanz that the audience perceives things quickly which are simple, clear, and ordered to understand.", "We need to be very careful while choosing colors and need to pick up the color sequence. Avoid using red and green color in the same graphics to guarantee the people who are color blind so they can easily distinguish the data.", "(Nelson, 2016) states that Tufte Lie Factor helps to evaluate how to perfectly present visuals. It means the size of the effect shown in the image should be equal to the size of the effect of the data. Your data should give a story.", "According to (Bernhard, 2012) do not label all the graphs and label only the important ones. It is good to erase redundant and non-ink data. Following such principles will facilitate a fast perception of the graphics for the audience. Please try to avoid gridlines.", "Please try to avoid using shadows in the graphics.", "Try to show data variation and avoid showing design variation.", "(Giard, 2011) states that gridlines should be removed, and also states vibrations are caused when it uses excessively in graphs which can be distracting for the audience.", "(Few, 2011) suggested that chart junk should be avoided. Decorating the interior of the graphics does not help the audience which is redundant data-ink and does not create any value. Please try to avoid using cosmetic decoration on the graphics. It also distracts viewers from understanding the data. Chart junk is good for visual but not for understanding the data.", "(Taylor, 2014) states mantra for the visual dashboard should start with an overview wherein a summary of the story should be given. Further, focus data using zoom in and drill down.", "Please try to implement the Mutually Exclusive and Collectively Exhaustive (MECE) technique for the story. In the story building, please take into consideration vertical and horizontal logic.", "In the narrative following questions should be taken into consideration:", "Data Visualization makes it easier to see trends and patterns from the data. Following the basic principles, everyone visually perceives objects easily. It helps portray the insights from data. It enables decision-makers to visually view data so that they can understand complex concepts or identify new patterns.", "\u25cfLundblad, P., noDate. Second Pillar of Mapping Data to Visualizations: Visual Encoding. Available from https://blog.qlik.com/visual-encoding", "\u25cfTaylor, T., 2014. How to Use the Information-Seeking Mantra in Cyber Intelligence Dashboards. Available from https://www.recordedfuture.com/information-seeking-mantra/", "\u25cf The New York Times, no date. Data visualization: basic principles. Available from http://paldhous.github.io/ucb/2016/dataviz/week2.html", "Now, take your thoughts on Twitter, Linkedin, and Github!!", "Agree or disagree with Saurav Singla\u2019s ideas and examples? Want to tell us your story?", "He is open to constructive feedback \u2014 if you have follow-up ideas for this analysis, comment it below or reach out!!", "Tweet @SauravSingla_08 , Comment Saurav_Singla , and Star SauravSingla right now!", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Senior Data Scientist | Author | Instructor | Mentor"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "h